<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 01 at 11:05PM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>..Areas of fog continue to develop across portions of deep south
Texas late tonight...
Surface observations and satellite images indicate areas of
fog...some locally dense...continue to develop across portions of
the Rio Grande Valley and northern ranchlands late tonight. Fog
will continue to develop across the area overnight as clear skies
and light winds allow the fog to continue to develop. Visibilities
will be reduced to 1 to 3 miles in general with isolated areas of
a quarter of a mile or less. If the fog becomes more widespread
and dense overnight...a Dense Fog Advisory will be needed for
portions of deep south Texas later tonight.
Motorists are urged to reduce speed...use low beam headlights...and
avoid following other vehicles too closely in areas of locally
dense fog.</description>
